The days where I’d rather stay in bed are more than the days where I actually feel like doing what I need to do to live my goals. Most days I feel like crap. Most days I’d rather watch tv all day. Most days I’d rather eat junk food.. 

BUT I DON’T. Instead, I CHOOSE to recommit to my commitments on a daily basis. 

“Don’t wanna train today”. Get up and do it anyway because healthy doesn’t sustain itself. 

“Don’t feel like talking to people today.” Do it anyway because connection gives us purpose. 

“Damn, that junk food sounds amazing..” It’s just a thought. I’d rather be fit so I’ll choose the better option instead. 

It’s not hard. It’s actually really simple. It just requires constant commitment. 

We are an accumulation of small decisions over a long period of time.
They say im obsessed and crazy. Well, I love being obsessed and crazy and healthy 😍💪🏽.

“Not giving a fuck does not mean being indifferent, it means being comfortable with being different.“ 

1 year ago exactly between the pics. I’ve lost a lot of “friends” and people over the years because my priorities evolved. I’ve learned that those meant to be in my life will be there. We always have a choice. In everything and anything we do. Most people choose the easy, comfortable choice day in and day out (partying every weekend, eating crap, toxic people, making excuses, etc). 

Very few choose to delay gratification. Very few take the path of constant discomfort. We choose what matters. But it’s a constant thing.

It doesn’t happen just once. It happens 24/7. 

Taking care of yourself is the BEST INVESTMENT you can make. Your body, your mind, it’s the only thing that’s really yours. 

Because in this world, NOTHING belongs to you except for the value you give yourself.

“El verdadero riesgo se halla en una vida sin riesgos.”

Cada mañana, la paz llega a tu puerta en forma de decisiones.  

En cada momento, tienes la opción de elegir tu actitud sin importar tus circunstancias. 

Estamos constantemente en busca de la felicidad.  La mayoría de la gente busca la felicidad en factores externos como en otras personas, algo materialista, un destino, un trabajo… por eso mucha gente es infeliz.  

La felicidad no existe en cosas externas.  La felicidad existe en ti y en nadie más.

Cuando dejas de buscar la validación externa, cuando dejas de compararte con lxs demás, cuando dejas de ser víctima de tus fracasos, cuando dejas de culpar a lxs demás y, en cambio, asumes total responsabilidad sobre tu vida, puedes encontrar la felicidad. 

Peace is within YOU.
Be a #stoic

No podemos controlar nada exterior.  No importa cuánto lo intentemos, cuánto insistamos, simplemente no podemos. 

Parte de la belleza de la vida es comprender eso, aceptarlo y luego aprender a enfocarnos únicamente en nuestro interior. 

Tratar de cambiar la opinión de otra persona o tratar de "hacer" que alguien haga algo es imposible.  Lo que se puede es impactar con empatía, amor y paciencia.  La influencia es nuestra, el resto no. 

BE A STOIC #stoic

What’s on the other side of that mountain has to be something you need more than anything in this world. It can’t just be something you want. 

You have to need it as bad as your need to breathe. There’s no other way. 

It’s not easy. It’s actually really fucking hard and when reality hits, you realize that nobody fucking cares about your millions of excuses as to why you’re miserable. 

You have to be willing to constantly delay gratification because great things take time. 

You have to be willing to deal with uncertainty and discomfort on a daily basis. 

A disciple of discipline. 

There’s no other way. It’s fucking worth it.
Excuses or results. YOU decide.

Somos muchxs lxs que luchamos contra estas barreras, algunxs luchan en silencio, otrxs en voz alta. Todas las formas de luchar son válidas. Sea como sea que te identifiques, es válido. 

PERTENECES. 

Yeah, I wish we didn’t need a PRIDE but we do. Because we’ve been institutionally, culturally, structurally, socially marginalized for too long. 

Siempre hemos existido. 

Si sientes que no tienes voz, estoy aquí para darte la mía.

Vivimos en un mundo “instantáneo” ..

YOU ARE WHAT YOU EAT. You are how you sleep. You are what you pay attention to. You are a combination of daily decisions over a long period of time. 

Building muscle mass take time. I’ve put on about 6 pounds of muscle over the past 2 years. 2 YEARS. be patient. Trust the process. Commit daily over a long period of time. 

Most people quit because they expect abs in 2 weeks or 2 months.. not guna happen unless you’re already relatively lean with an adequate amount of muscle.

It’s really about creating sustainable habits to meet your objectives. The process is different for everyone. Don’t compare yourself. But yeah, use others as inspiration or whatever you need.. 

most days when I wake up, I feel pretty damn good about myself. Mentally, emotionally, physically. That’s what matters. LONGEVITY. HEALTHY habits.

“Damn, you’re so lucky you’re fit. You’re so lucky you have time to go to the gym. You’re so lucky you have good genes“.. !! It’s not luck. It’s not genes. 

Weak minded people make comments like that. It takes years of discipline, commitment, intentional lifestyle choices, day in and day out in order to create an OUTSTANDING LIFESTYLE. 

It takes daily sacrifice over years. 

You’re out drinking alcohol? I’m sleeping 

You’re out overeating daily? I’m making conscious, educated nutrition choices 

You’re saying you don’t have time ? we all have the same 24 hours in a day, we all have stress, we all have bills, we all have responsibilities, we all have CHOICE. I choose wisely. 

You blame your circumstances ? I make the best of mine

You quit after week 3 ? I’ve been doing this for YEARS 

You want instant results ? They don’t exist 

You’re too proud to ask for help? VULNERABILITY is where legends are born 

You want to be better ? YOU CAN BE

Anything that’s already been done can be done again. MAKE IT HAPPEN.

“Si quieres cambiar el mundo, empieza por tender tu cama…. 

Si quieres cambiar el mundo, mide a una persona por el tamaño de su corazón, no por el tamaño de sus aletas. La vida está llena de circos. fallarás….

Probablemente fracasarás con frecuencia. Será doloroso. Será desalentador. A veces te pondrá a prueba hasta lo más profundo.

Pero si quieres cambiar el mundo, no tengas miedo de los circos. Hay muchos tiburones en el mundo. Si esperas completar el nado, tendrás que lidiar con ellos…

Entonces, si quieres cambiar el mundo, no retrocedas ante los tiburones. Si algo he aprendido en mi tiempo viajando por el mundo es el poder de la esperanza. El poder de una persona (Washington, Lincoln, King, Mandela e incluso una joven de Pakistán, Malala) puede cambiar el mundo dando esperanza a la gente.

Entonces, si quieres cambiar el mundo, empieza a cantar cuando estés metido en el barro hasta el cuello…

Sepas que la vida no es justa y que fracasarás con frecuencia. Pero si tomas algunos riesgos, avanzas cuando los tiempos son más difíciles, enfrentas a los acosadores, levantas a los oprimidos y nunca, jamás te rindes; si haces estas cosas, entonces la próxima generación y las generaciones siguientes vivirán en un mundo mucho mejor que el que tenemos hoy.”

-“Make Your Bed”
